        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "To paraphrase Ann Lamott:",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "'Metaphors work by framing the unknown in terms of the known.'",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "To use whatever resonates. Whatever works.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "It’s not that these comparisons are literal or real. (They’re certainly not.)",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "It’s that we are bred to understand with story. To feel through images. And to see through patterns.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}